<h3>Systems thinking</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Reasoning about how parts of a system connect and influence each other. Sees the whole, not just individual parts.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A diagram with nodes and arrows showing connections.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Systems thinking helps us understand that fixing one part of an ecosystem can have unexpected effects elsewhere."</p>
