</table>

<h3>Greenhouse effect</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> The way certain gases in an atmosphere trap heat, warming the planet. Natural greenhouse effect makes Earth livable; human-enhanced greenhouse effect causes warming.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A planet with sunlight entering, infrared bouncing back, and greenhouse gases trapping some of it.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Without the greenhouse effect, Earth would be ~33°C colder and frozen."</p>
