<h2 id="u2">Unit 2 — Surface Processes &amp; Reading the Landscape <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--muted);font-size:14px;">(13 terms)</span></h2>

<h3>Weathering (mechanical, chemical)</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Breakdown of rocks at Earth's surface. Mechanical = physical breaking (frost, wind); chemical = chemical reactions (dissolution, rust).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Rock fragments next to a smooth piece + a rusty piece.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Tropical chemical weathering is dramatic in Chennai's climate — high humidity accelerates rock breakdown."</p>
