</table>

<h3>Deposition</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Settling and accumulation of sediment in a new location after erosion. Builds beaches, deltas, river floodplains.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A river slowing down and depositing its load.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "The Cauvery delta is built from millions of years of fluvial deposition."</p>
