</table>

<h3>Sediment</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Loose particles (sand, silt, clay) produced by weathering and transported by erosion. Becomes sedimentary rock over time.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Layers of sand and mud.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Heavy monsoon runoff carries enormous amounts of sediment from the Western Ghats to the coast."</p>
