<h2 id="u3">Unit 3 — Plate Tectonics &amp; Natural Hazards <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--muted);font-size:14px;">(18 terms)</span></h2>

<h3>Plate (tectonic)</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A large segment of Earth's outer shell (lithosphere) that moves slowly over the asthenosphere below. ~15 major plates cover Earth.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A jigsaw-puzzle map of Earth with major plates outlined.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "The Pacific Plate subducts beneath the Okhotsk Plate near Japan, causing megathrust earthquakes."</p>
