</table>

<h3>Convergent boundary</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Where two plates push toward each other. Produces earthquakes, mountain building (Himalayas), or subduction (volcanic arcs).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Two arrows pointing toward each other; one plate diving below.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Japan sits on a convergent boundary where the Pacific Plate dives beneath the Okhotsk Plate."</p>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Tamil</th><th>Hindi</th><th>Français</th><th>Korean</th><th>Japanese</th></tr></thead>
