</table>

<h3>Divergent boundary</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Where two plates pull apart. Produces mid-ocean ridges, sea-floor spreading, rift valleys.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Two arrows pointing away from each other; magma rising in the gap.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "The Mid-Atlantic Ridge is a divergent boundary creating new ocean floor."</p>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Tamil</th><th>Hindi</th><th>Français</th><th>Korean</th><th>Japanese</th></tr></thead>
