</table>

<h3>Transform boundary</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Where two plates slide past each other horizontally. Produces strike-slip earthquakes (like Kobe 1995, San Andreas).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Two plates with horizontal arrows in opposite directions; sliding past.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "The Anatolian Fault under Istanbul is a transform boundary; like San Andreas, it produces shaking but no tsunamis."</p>
