</table>

<h3>Subduction</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> When one plate dives beneath another at a convergent boundary. Produces megathrust earthquakes, tsunamis, stratovolcanoes.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Cross-section showing oceanic plate sliding under continental plate.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "The Tōhoku 2011 megathrust earthquake was caused by subduction of the Pacific Plate."</p>
