<h3>Megathrust</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A very large earthquake at a subduction zone, where the entire interface ruptures. Largest earthquakes on Earth (M9+).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A subduction zone with the locked interface suddenly slipping.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Tōhoku 2011 (M9.1) was one of the largest megathrust events ever recorded."</p>
