<h3>Stratovolcano</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A tall, steep-sided volcano made of alternating layers of lava and ash. Produces explosive eruptions and pyroclastic flows. (Vesuvius, Pinatubo, Merapi.)</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Classic cone-shaped volcano with smoke.</p>
