<h3>Pyroclastic flow</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A fast-moving avalanche of hot gas + rock (700°C+) from a volcanic eruption. Unsurvivable up close. Engineering can't stop it; only distance + warning.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Volcano with red-orange cloud rushing down its side.</p>
