</table>

<h3>Greenhouse gas (GHG)</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Atmospheric gases that trap heat — CO₂, methane, water vapor, others. Strengthens the natural greenhouse effect, causing warming.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Atmosphere with molecules of CO₂, CH₄ trapping outgoing heat.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "CO₂ is the most important long-term GHG; methane is more potent but shorter-lived."</p>
