</table>

<h3>Carbon cycle</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> The movement of carbon between atmosphere, oceans, land, and life. Includes both natural cycling and human emissions.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Diagram with arrows showing CO₂ moving between atmosphere, plants, ocean, soil, and underground.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Human activity (fossil fuel burning) has added carbon to the atmospheric pool faster than the natural cycle can absorb it."</p>
