</table>

<h3>Net-zero</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Total emissions = total removals. A net-zero economy adds no net new greenhouse gases to the atmosphere.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A balance scale: emissions on one side, removals on the other, balanced.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "India has committed to net-zero by 2070; many cities aim for 2050."</p>
