</table>

<h3>Sequestration</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Removing CO₂ from the atmosphere and storing it (in plants, soil, oceans, or technology).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A tree absorbing CO₂; an arrow into a long-term storage location.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Mangrove sequestration is among the most concentrated forms of natural carbon storage."</p>
