</table>

<h3>Tribunal / Treaty</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Tribunal = legal body that adjudicates disputes (like the Cauvery Tribunal). Treaty = formal agreement between countries (like the Indus Waters Treaty).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Two contrasting images: courtroom (tribunal) vs. signing ceremony (treaty).</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "The Cauvery Tribunal made allocation rulings; the Indus Treaty is a country-to-country water agreement."</p>
