</table>

<h3>Position (in policy sense)</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A stakeholder's specific stance on a contested issue. Different from "opinion" — a position is a developed argument backed by evidence.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Two stakeholders facing each other across a table, each holding a position paper.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "My Position Paper argues from the perspective of a Cauvery delta farmer — that position is rooted in specific evidence and interests."</p>
