</table>

<h3>Compromise</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> An agreement where each side gives up something to reach a workable outcome. Different from "winning" — both sides may be partially unsatisfied.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Two stakeholders meeting in the middle, each giving up some demand.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Real water disputes rarely have full agreement — workable compromises are often the best outcome."</p>
