</table>

<h3>Trophic level</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A position in the food chain: producers (plants), primary consumers (herbivores), secondary consumers (predators of herbivores), tertiary consumers (top predators).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Pyramid with plants at base, herbivores above, then predators.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Eating meat puts humans at a higher trophic level than eating grains — and uses much more energy."</p>
