</table>

<h3>Carrying capacity</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> The maximum population an ecosystem can sustainably support, given its resources.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A graph showing population growing, then leveling off at a ceiling.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Modern industrial agriculture has raised Earth's apparent carrying capacity for humans — but at long-term ecological cost."</p>
