</table>

<h3>Monoculture vs. Agroforestry</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Monoculture = growing a single crop on a large area (high yield, low biodiversity). Agroforestry = mixing crops + trees (moderate yield, higher biodiversity + resilience).</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Side-by-side: vast field of corn vs. shaded coffee under trees.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Iowa corn-soy = monoculture; Western Ghats shade coffee = agroforestry."</p>
