</table>

<h3>Conservation vs. Restoration</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Conservation = protecting existing ecosystems. Restoration = bringing back degraded ecosystems. Both are needed.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> Conservation = a wall around an intact forest. Restoration = green growth coming back on bare land.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "The Pichavaram mangroves combine conservation of intact areas + restoration of degraded zones."</p>
