</table>

<h3>Trade-off</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> When gaining one thing means giving up another. Real-world decisions are full of trade-offs.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A scale with one side rising as the other falls.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Land Plans involve trade-offs — maximizing food usually reduces biodiversity."</p>
