<h2 id="u7">Unit 7 — Energy, Pollution &amp; Sustainability <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--muted);font-size:14px;">(14 terms)</span></h2>

<h3>Energy vs. Power</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Energy = capacity to do work (measured in Joules, kWh). Power = rate of using energy (measured in Watts, MW). Different things!</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A bucket of water (energy) + the rate at which it pours (power).</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "A 1000 W appliance uses 1 kWh in one hour — different units measuring different things."</p>
