</table>

<h3>Watt (kWh, MW, GW, TWh)</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Units of power and energy. 1 kW = 1000 W; kWh = energy used at 1 kW for 1 hour; MW = megawatt = 1 million W; GW = gigawatt = 1 billion W; TWh = terawatt-hour.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A scale showing W → kW → MW → GW → TW with examples.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Chennai's peak electricity demand can exceed 6,000 MW — equivalent to 6,000 large household stoves running simultaneously."</p>
