<h3>Intermittency</h3>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> When energy generation isn't constant — solar doesn't shine at night, wind doesn't blow on demand. The central challenge for renewables.</p>
<p><strong>Visual cue:</strong> A graph of solar generation: high midday, zero at night.</p>
<p><strong>In a sentence:</strong> "Intermittency creates the need for energy storage + flexible grids."</p>
